.SH NAME
.P
rpm_db_snooper - A systemd service to monitor process termination signals related to the RPM database
.P
.SH SYNOPSIS
.P
rpm_db_snooper.service
.P
General systemd command can be used to start or restart the service for more info see \fBsystemd(1)\fR man page
.P
.SH DESCRIPTION
.P
\fBrpm_db_snooper\fR is a systemd service to monitor on process termination signals related to the RPM database, providing insights into potential issues and improve system maintenance.
.P
.SH FILES
The following files are relevant to the rpm_db_snooper command:
.P
/var/lib/rpm
.RS 4
The default location of the RPM database.
.P
.RE
/usr/libexec/oled-tools/scripts.d/monitor_rpmdb.d
.RS 4
DTrace program that monitors the RPM database for any changes made by the yum, dnf, or rpm commands.
.P
.RE
/var/log/messages
.RS 4
Diagnostic information will be written to this file from rpm_db_snooper service
.P
.RE
journalctl -u rpm_db_snooper.service
.RS 4
Journalctl can also be used with the service to filter out the logs related to rpm_db_snooper.
.P
.RE
The diagnostic information can be accessed using \fBjournalctl\fR command. The diagnostic information are logged under the \fBSYSLOG_IDENTIFIER\fR "rpm_db_snooper".
The \fBrpm_db_snooper\fR command is a wrapper for the \fBmonitor_rpmdb.d\fR DTrace program.
.P
To enable the debug logging in the \fBrpm_db_snooper\fR command, set the \fBRPM_DB_SNOOPER_DEBUG\fR environment variable to \fB-DDEBUG\fR.
It is also possible to enable the debug logging in the \fBmonitor_rpmdb.d\fR DTrace program by setting the \fBDEBUG\fR environment variable in the \fBmonitor_rpmdb.d\fR DTrace program
or invoke the \fBmonitor_rpmdb.d\fR dtrace program using the \fBdtrace\fR command with the \fB-DDEBUG\fR flag.
.P
